{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/221/syllabusWQ09.html", "content": "<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01\rTransitional//EN\">\r<html>\r<head>\r  <meta content=\"text/html; charset=iso-8859-1\"\rhttp-equiv=\"Content-Type\">\r  <meta http-equiv=\"Author\" content=\"Richard N. Taylor\">\r  <meta content=\"Taylor IN4MATX 211\" name=\"KeyWords\"><title>IN4MATX 221 Winter 2009</title>\r\r  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\">\r  <style type=\"text/css\">\r<!--\r.style1 {color: #666666}\r.style2 {color: #000000}\r-->\r  </style>\r</head>\r\r\r<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><font face=\"Verdana\">\r\rInformatics 221: Software Architecture </font></h2>\r<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r  <p><font face=\"Verdana\"><b>\r  Winter Quarter 2009</b></font></p>\r  <p><strong><font face=\"Verdana\">Course Code 37215 </font></strong></p>\r  <p><i>Last update:\r      <!-- #BeginDate format:Am1 -->March 12, 2009<!-- #EndDate -->\r  </i></p>\r</div>\r\r&nbsp;<br>\r\r\r<table width=\"60%\" cellspacing=\"8\">\r<tbody>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\">\r\t<p>\r\r\t<b>Instructor:</b></p>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\t<a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/%7Etaylor/\">Richard N. Taylor </a>\r\t</p>\r\r</td>\r</tr>\r\r<tr>\r\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\t<b>Email:</b></p>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\t(taylor [at] ics [dot] uci [dot] edu)<br>\r\tTo ensure a response to your email, please include\r\"Informatics 221\" in the\r\tsubject line and send your email from a UCI\raccount.\r\t</p>\r\r</td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\r\t<b>Office hours:</b>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r<td> After class, or by email appointment<br>\r\r</td>\r\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<p>\r\t<b>Lectures: </b></font>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<p>\r\r\tTuesday and Thursday 3:30 - 4:50 p.m.<strong>,</strong> PSCB 220 (Building #413)</p>\r\r</td>\r</tr>\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<b>Web site:</b>\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<a\rhref=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/221/syllabusWQ09.html\">http://www.ics.uci.edu/~taylor/classes/221/syllabusWQ09.html</a></td>\r\r</tr>\r\r<!--\r<tr>\r<td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\">\r\t<b>EEE Noteboard:</b>\r\r</td>\r<td>\r\t<a\rhref=\"http://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/noteboard/index.php?board=2607\">http://eee.uci.edu/toolbox/noteboard/index.php?board=2607</a><br>\r\t</p>\r</td>\r</tr>\r-->\r\r</tbody>\r</table>\r\r\r<h3>What's New? </h3>\r<ul>\r  <li>[January 5, 2009] Website goes live on EEE. </li>\r</ul>\r<p><font face=\"Verdana\"><font size=\"-1\"><a\rhref=\"#description\">Description</a>\r  - <font face=\"Verdana\"><a href=\"#readings\">Textbook and Readings</a> - </font><a href=\"#schedule\">Schedule</a> - <a\rhref=\"#grading\">Grading</a> - <a\rhref=\"#policies\">Policies</a>\r  \r  </font>\r</font></p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<h3>\r<a name=\"description\"></a><b>Description</b></font></h3>\r<p><b><a\rhref=\"http://www.editor.uci.edu/07-08/ics/ics.7.htm\">Catalog\rdescription:</a></b></p>\r\r<p>Study of the concepts, representation techniques, development methods, and\r  tools for architecture-centric software engineering. Topics include domain-specific\r  software architectures, architectural styles, architecture description languages,\rsoftware connectors, and dynamism in architectures. Formerly ICS 223.</p>\r<p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r<a name=\"readings\" id=\"readings\"></a>\r<h3>Textbook (REQUIRED)</h3>\r<p><strong>Software Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice.</strong> Richard\r  N. Taylor, Nenad Medvidovic, and Eric M. Dashofy. Copyright &copy; 2010 John\r  Wiley &amp; Sons, Inc. (ISBN-13: 978-0470-16774-8)</p>\r<ul>\r  <li><a href=\"http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0470167742.html\">Software\r      Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice</a> at Wiley.com, the publisher's\r      site</li>\r  <li><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Software-Architecture-Foundations-Theory-Practice/dp/0470167742\">Software\r      Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice</a> at Amazon.com</li>\r  <li><a href=\"http://search.barnesandnoble.com/Software-Architecture/Richard-N-Taylor/e/9780470167748/?itm=1\">Software\r      Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice</a> at Barnes and Noble</li>\r</ul>\r<p>&nbsp;</p>\r<hr width=\"100%\">\r\r<h3><font face=\"Verdana\"><a\rname=\"schedule\"></a>Schedule</font></h3>\r\r<p>\rThe schedule is <em>subject to change</em>.&nbsp;\r<table width=100% height=\"968\" border=1 cellpadding=\"3\">\r\r  <tr>\r  \t<th width=\"7%\">Week</th>\r  \t<th colspan=\"2\">Date</th>\r  \t<th width=\"34%\">Topic</th>\r  \t<th width=\"34%\">Individual Class Topics</th>\r\r  \t<th width=\"13%\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\"><span class=\"style2\">Readings</span></th>\r\r  \t<th width=\"18%\" bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Homework</th>\r  </tr>\r<tr>\r  <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 1    <td width=\"7%\" rowspan=\"8\" class=\"date\">  <p align=\"center\">J</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">A</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">N</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">U</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">A</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">R</p>\r    <p align=\"center\">Y</p>\r    <td width=\"7%\" class=\"date\">6 Tu \r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Introduction    </td>\r    <td><a href=\"01_The_Big_Idea.ppt\">The Big Idea </a></td>\r  <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 1       \r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td class=\"date\">8&nbsp;Th\r    <td><a href=\"02_Architectures_In_Context.ppt\">Architectures in Context</a>     \r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 2     \r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" class=\"due\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td rowspan=\"2\" class=\"week\"> 2    <!-- - - - - - - -3- - - - - - - -->\r    <td class=\"date\">13&nbsp;Tu\r    <td rowspan=\"2\">Basic Concepts and Introduction to Design     </td>\r    <td><a href=\"03_Basic_Concepts.ppt\">Basic Concepts</a> </td>\r\r    <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">Chapter 3 </td>\r      <td bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\">&nbsp;</td>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    